# 4. BAYES’ THEOREM

Bayesian Networks are based on Bayes’ Theorem.

Formula:

P(A|B) = [P(B|A) × P(A)] / P(B)

Where:

* P(A|B) = Posterior probability
* P(B|A) = Likelihood
* P(A) = Prior probability
* P(B) = Evidence probability

